      • kappa

        public static double kappa​(java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,​net.sf.javaml.classification.evaluation.PerformanceMeasure> results)
        This method implements the Kappa statistic [1], which measures inter-rater agreement for qualitative (categorical) items.

        [1] J. Cohen. A coefficient of agreement for nominal scales. Educational and Psychological Measurement, 20(1):37-46, 1960. https://doi.org/10.1177/001316446002000104
        Parameters:
        results - The results of classifier evaluation
        Returns:
        The Kappa coefficient

      • kappa

                           net.sf.javaml.core.Dataset testData)
        This method implements the Kappa statistic [1], which measures inter-rater agreement for qualitative (categorical) items.

        [1] J. Cohen. A coefficient of agreement for nominal scales. Educational and Psychological Measurement, 20(1):37-46, 1960. https://doi.org/10.1177/001316446002000104
        Parameters:
        cls - The classifier to test
        testData - The data set to test on
        Returns:
        The Kappa coefficient

      • sensitivity

        public static double sensitivity​(java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,​net.sf.javaml.classification.evaluation.PerformanceMeasure> results,
                                 java.lang.Object label)
        This method implements sensitivity of a classification. As sensitivity is defined for binary classifications, this method implements the one against all approach, thus it is necessary to provide the label of the class to be tested
        Parameters:
        results - The results of classifier evaluation
        label - The class label
        Returns:
        The sensitivity index (of 0 if label is not a valid class)
